{"_id":"002734877d460f9a","name":"Full Send","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Yolei","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Love rank 3+)","description":"Once per encounter as a Basic Action, choose one ally Digimon within 4 spaces. They immediately gain +3 to their next attack roll and +3 damage on that attack. This must be used before they attack, not after. You back people completely or not at all."}}
{"_id":"017a18bff58252d1","name":"Kendo Stance","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Cody","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Reliability rank 3+)","description":"Once per encounter at the start of your turn you may declare Kendo Stance. Until the start of your next turn your Digimon gains +3 to their Reliability stat. They take hits better when you are composed. Stance ends if your Digimon attacks â€” committing to a strike means leaving the defensive position."}}
{"_id":"02e6afcbf8984c1a","name":"Prepared This Time","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"TK S2","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Hope pool 20+ (any crest rank 4+)","description":"At the start of each encounter before turns begin, you may spend 3 Hope to grant your Digimon temporary HP equal to your highest crest stat rank. You saw what unpreparedness cost last time. You planned for it."}}
{"_id":"0341b247c6ef11d8","name":"Unstoppable","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Davis","row":4,"expCost":1000,"requirements":"Both Row 3 abilities, Courage rank 7","description":"Once per session you may declare Unstoppable at the start of your turn. For the rest of this round your Digimon cannot be reduced below 1 HP by any attack, cannot be affected by any status effect, and their attacks cannot miss â€” every attack roll is treated as a hit regardless of the result. Natural 1s still deal no damage but the attack connects. One round. Absolute. Nothing stops them."}}
{"_id":"0640b675dab91a8b","name":"Anchor","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kari S2","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Steadying Presence, Sincerity rank 4","description":"Steadying Presence now also grants all friendly Digimon on the field resistance to Confuse and Blind status effects â€” if either would be applied they may immediately reroll the triggering effect with +3. Kari keeps people from coming apart. Quietly. Completely."}}
{"_id":"0de3edb509aa9e1c","name":"Still Waters","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kari S2","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Voice of Light, Love rank 5","description":"Once per session as your Basic Action, choose one enemy Digimon. Make a Tame check â€” on a success that Digimon becomes completely passive for 2 rounds. They do not attack, move, or use abilities. If the affected Digimon takes any damage during this time the effect ends immediately and they return to normal. At the end of the 2 rounds they also return to normal. Kari does not always need her partner to win a fight. Sometimes she just needs a moment."}}
{"_id":"11bfee208d304b93","name":"Control Freak","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kaiser","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Dark Spiral, Knowledge rank 5","description":"Dark Spiral can now be used on two targets simultaneously in the same action. Both targets must be within 4 spaces. Make one Command check â€” if it succeeds both targets are affected. The Kaiser never wastes a move on one problem when one move can solve two."}}
{"_id":"17b628bf04fb0460","name":"Rally Point","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"TK S2","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Prepared This Time, Hope pool 25+","description":"Once per encounter as a Basic Action, choose one allied Digimon that is below half their max HP. They immediately restore HP equal to your Hope pool divided by 5, rounded down. You always know who needs it most."}}
{"_id":"1acdd20707d46d15","name":"Genius For Good","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Ken Redeemed","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Wormmon's Trust, Knowledge rank 4","description":"Once per encounter as a Free Action, choose one ally Digimon about to make an attack. They gain +Knowledge rank to their damage roll on that attack. You still see every angle. Now you use that to help instead."}}
{"_id":"1e6f65926a80df8b","name":"Measured Step","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Cody","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Reliability rank 3+)","description":"Once per encounter as a Free Action on your turn, choose one enemy within 4 spaces of your Digimon. Make a Zero Error check DN 12. On a success you identify the optimal attack angle â€” your Digimon's next attack against that enemy ignores half their Love stat damage reduction, rounded down."}}
{"_id":"2c243c5fcec61597","name":"Heart on Her Sleeve","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Yolei","row":4,"expCost":1000,"requirements":"Both Row 3 abilities, Love rank 7","description":"Once per session at the start of your turn you may declare Heart on Her Sleeve. Choose one ally Tamer. For the rest of this encounter all of their Digimon's attack rolls and damage rolls use the higher of their own stat or yours. Your passion becomes their strength. You give everything you have and somehow it is exactly enough."}}
{"_id":"2c3495771b10b941","name":"Wormmon's Trust","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Ken Redeemed","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Friendship rank 3+)","description":"Your Digimon gains +2 to all attack rolls when fighting alongside at least one ally Digimon. The bond is real now. It was always supposed to be. This is what it feels like when it actually is."}}
{"_id":"2ead4e6d38190254","name":"Sheer Stubbornness","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Davis","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Never Back Down, Courage rank 4","description":"When your Digimon would be Paralyzed, Frozen, or Confused, they may make a Reinforce check DN 12 before the status applies. On a success the status is completely negated. On a failure it applies as normal. Davis Tamers do not stay down."}}
{"_id":"39c6d94081b414c7","name":"Genius Protocol","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kaiser","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"At least 1 Row 1 ability, Knowledge rank 5","description":"Once per encounter as a Free Action, you may declare one specific move an enemy Digimon used this round. Until the end of the encounter your Digimon takes half damage from that move. You watched. You adapted. You already have the counter."}}
{"_id":"3cdbf545131c8911","name":"Bounce Back","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Yolei","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Emotional Spike, Love rank 5","description":"When your Digimon takes damage that would reduce them below half their max HP, they immediately restore HP equal to your Love rank. This triggers once per encounter and automatically â€” you do not need to declare it. She always finds her footing again."}}
{"_id":"46de8399e24b7e70","name":"Tunnel Vision","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Davis","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Gogglehead, Courage rank 4","description":"While your Digimon has an active focus target from Gogglehead, they also gain +2 to all attack rolls against that target. The bonus does not apply to any other target. You have one goal. That is enough."}}
{"_id":"57bbf1d906edda13","name":"Take the Hit","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Ken Redeemed","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Friendship rank 3+)","description":"Once per encounter when an ally Digimon within 4 spaces is targeted by an attack, you may declare Take the Hit before the roll resolves. Your Digimon moves up to 4 spaces toward the ally and receives the attack instead â€” including all damage and status effects. The ally is completely unaffected. You step in front of harm now. Every time."}}
{"_id":"5a0118d64af9f936","name":"Fierce Loyalty","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Yolei","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Full Send, Love rank 4","description":"Full Send now also removes one status effect from the chosen ally Digimon when activated. You boost them and you fix them at the same time. Anyone you back gets everything."}}
{"_id":"64ffaa6fbb21d331","name":"All or Nothing","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Yolei","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Fierce Loyalty, Love rank 5","description":"Once per session as your Basic Action, choose one allied Digimon. Until the end of the round they deal double damage on every hit. At the end of the round they gain the Paralyze 2 status â€” the effort costs them. The gamble is always worth it."}}
{"_id":"6c9b3597bd8eca7a","name":"Absolute Dominance","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kaiser","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Control Freak, Knowledge rank 6","description":"Once per encounter when your Digimon defeats an enemy Digimon, all remaining enemies within 3 spaces of the defeated Digimon gain the Paralyze 1 status. They saw what happened. They hesitate. Fear is a resource. The Kaiser uses all of them."}}
{"_id":"7565bc6f4078d04e","name":"Counter Strike","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Cody","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Hold the Line, Reliability rank 5","description":"While Kendo Stance is active, when your Digimon is attacked and the attack misses, they may immediately make a free Basic Attack against the attacker as a Free Action. This does not end Kendo Stance. Patience is not passivity."}}
{"_id":"7a971fb5898746e6","name":"Making It Right","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Ken Redeemed","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Take the Hit, Friendship rank 4","description":"Once per session at the start of an encounter, choose one ally Digimon. Remove all negative status effects from them immediately before the first turn begins. You cannot undo the past. You can make sure they start clean."}}
{"_id":"80be2e066fc441ce","name":"Voice of Light","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kari S2","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Gentle Command, Love rank 4","description":"Gentle Command can now target two non-boss enemy Digimon in the same action â€” both must be within 4 spaces. Make one Tame check against both. If it succeeds both are affected. If it fails neither is. The reach of her presence is wider than anyone expects."}}
{"_id":"900017008f78e51e","name":"Human Shield","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Ken Redeemed","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Making It Right, Friendship rank 5","description":"Take the Hit can now be used twice per encounter instead of once. Additionally when you use Take the Hit, your Digimon gains temporary HP equal to your Friendship rank before the attack resolves â€” a small buffer between them and what is coming. You have gotten very good at this. You do not intend to stop."}}
{"_id":"9ab86c346e86e3c4","name":"Never Back Down","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Davis","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Courage rank 3+)","description":"Once per encounter when your Digimon fails an attack roll, they may immediately make the same attack again for free as part of the same action. The second roll uses the same target but counts as a separate attack. Missing twice means you try harder next time â€” not that you stop."}}
{"_id":"a0270d65c36f6add","name":"Read the Situation Wrong","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Yolei","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Love rank 3+)","description":"Once per encounter when you use a skill check and fail, you may immediately reroll it. If the second roll also fails, gain +2 to your next skill check this encounter â€” the embarrassment makes you sharper. Yolei's mistakes have a habit of teaching her something."}}
{"_id":"a0e322277a3fe982","name":"Steadying Presence","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kari S2","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Sincerity rank 3","description":"Once per session at the start of an encounter, all friendly Digimon on the field immediately remove all negative status effects before the first turn begins. You do not make noise. You do not make speeches. You simply being there makes everyone steadier."}}
{"_id":"a9f6e437f58a2063","name":"Gogglehead","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Davis","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Courage rank 3+)","description":"Once per encounter you may declare a target as your Digimon's focus. Until the end of the encounter your Digimon deals +2 damage to that target on every hit. Switching focus costs your Free Action. You cannot focus on something without going all in."}}
{"_id":"ad20348949b8c4d6","name":"Crest of Kindness","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Ken Redeemed","row":4,"expCost":1000,"requirements":"Both Row 3 abilities, Friendship rank 7","description":"Once per session when you use Take the Hit, you may activate Crest of Kindness. Your Digimon takes no damage and suffers no status effects from that attack â€” the hit is completely absorbed. Nothing gets through. Not this time. Ken spent years being the reason people got hurt. He has decided that is finished."}}
{"_id":"b0e3f7523adeb1cd","name":"Unbroken Code","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Cody","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"At least 1 Row 2 ability, Reliability rank 5","description":"Once per encounter when your Digimon is targeted by a Confuse, Blind, or Freeze status effect, you may make a Firewall check DN 14 as a Free Action off-turn. On a success the status is completely negated. Cody's principles extend to his partner. What he will not let break in himself, he will not let break in them."}}
{"_id":"b88722debe158288","name":"Dark Spiral","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kaiser","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Knowledge rank 4+)","description":"Once per encounter as a Basic Action, target one enemy Digimon within 4 spaces. Make a Command check DN 12. On a success that Digimon takes -2 to all attack rolls and -2 to their Reliability until the end of the encounter â€” their own instincts are working against them. The Kaiser does not defeat enemies. He degrades them."}}
{"_id":"c16f4d47760f9d57","name":"Hold the Line","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Cody","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Kendo Stance, Reliability rank 4","description":"While Kendo Stance is active your Digimon also gains +2 to all attack rolls. You are not hiding behind that wall â€” you are waiting for the right moment to strike through it."}}
{"_id":"c38db6806b8b1a64","name":"The Right Moment","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"TK S2","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Keep Going, Hope pool 30+","description":"Once per session you may use your Free Action to hold your turn. At any point before your next turn begins you may interrupt any other character's action â€” ally or enemy â€” to act immediately. Move, use an item, digivolve, anything except attack. TK has learned when to wait and when to move."}}
{"_id":"c497347cc281830f","name":"Digimon Emperor","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kaiser","row":4,"expCost":1000,"requirements":"Both Row 3 abilities, Knowledge rank 8","description":"Once per session at the start of your turn you may activate Digimon Emperor. Until the end of the encounter all enemies within 6 spaces take -3 to all attack rolls and -3 to their Reliability. All allies within 6 spaces gain +3 to all attack rolls. The Kaiser does not fight battles. He decides their outcomes before they begin. The field is his. Every piece on it moves because he permits it."}}
{"_id":"cc5b4e1c48b20ed5","name":"Unshakeable","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kari S2","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Anchor, Sincerity rank 5","description":"Once per encounter as a Free Action off-turn when an allied Digimon would gain a negative status effect, you may spend 3 Hope to completely negate it. The effect never applies. This can be used on any allied Digimon within 6 spaces. You hold people together. You have always held people together."}}
{"_id":"cf623607106391d5","name":"No Escape","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kaiser","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Genius Protocol, Knowledge rank 6","description":"Once per encounter as a Free Action after an enemy Digimon moves, you may force them to stop 1 space short of their intended destination. Make a Command check DN 14. On a success their movement ends immediately. They do not go where they planned. They go where you allow."}}
{"_id":"d009081d23575681","name":"Calculated Cruelty","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kaiser","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Entry requirement met (Knowledge rank 4+)","description":"When your Digimon attacks an enemy that is currently affected by any status effect, they deal +Knowledge rank bonus damage. You target the already-broken. Efficiency is not callousness. It is just better tactics."}}
{"_id":"d2c25e3fa37637fc","name":"Keep Going","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"TK S2","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"Not Flinching, Hope pool 25+","description":"Once per encounter when your Digimon would revert due to Hope running out, you may spend any amount of remaining Hope â€” even 0 â€” to delay the reversion by 1 round. This can only be used once per encounter. One more round. You always find one more round."}}
{"_id":"d3005f9f6d61ac0d","name":"Light It Up","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"TK S2","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Rally Point, Hope pool 30+","description":"Once per session at the start of your turn you may declare Light It Up. All allied Digimon immediately restore HP equal to your highest crest stat rank. All allied Tamers restore 5 Hope. This does not cost an action. Hope is not a resource TK hoards. It is something he gives away."}}
{"_id":"d49a379850fdd50a","name":"Calculated Response","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Cody","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"At least 1 Row 1 ability, Reliability rank 4","description":"Once per encounter when your Digimon is attacked and takes damage, you may use your Free Action to immediately make a Zero Error check DN 12. On a success your Digimon's next attack this round deals bonus damage equal to the damage they just received, up to a maximum of your Reliability rank x 2. You absorb information. You respond precisely."}}
{"_id":"d4e0f51157c5f0b4","name":"Radiance","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kari S2","row":4,"expCost":1000,"requirements":"Both Row 3 abilities, Love rank 6 AND Sincerity rank 6","description":"Once per session as a Basic Action, activate Radiance. Every enemy Digimon within 6 spaces must make a Firewall check DN 15. On a failure they cannot target any allied Digimon until the start of your next turn â€” they may still move and act freely but any attack aimed at an ally automatically misses regardless of the roll. Boss Digimon make this check but are not immune to failure. The light does not ask permission."}}
{"_id":"dae57dbfde72077b","name":"Perfect Form","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Cody","row":4,"expCost":1000,"requirements":"Both Row 3 abilities, Reliability rank 7","description":"Once per session at the start of your turn you may activate Perfect Form. For the rest of this encounter Kendo Stance no longer ends when your Digimon attacks â€” you maintain the defensive position through every strike. Your Digimon gains the full benefits of Kendo Stance and Hold the Line permanently for the duration, and Counter Strike triggers on every miss regardless of whether you declared the stance this turn. Cody does not reach Perfect Form. Perfect Form is simply what Cody looks like when he stops holding back."}}
{"_id":"df37b322928fdf89","name":"Gentle Command","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Kari S2","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Love rank 3","description":"Once per encounter as a Basic Action, choose one non-boss enemy Digimon within 4 spaces. Make a Tame check DN 13. On a success that Digimon skips their next turn entirely â€” not stunned, not confused, simply still. They felt something in her presence and could not move against it. On a failure nothing happens and the action is spent."}}
{"_id":"e1d4449832f068d2","name":"Fortress","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"TK S2","row":4,"expCost":1000,"requirements":"Both Row 3 abilities, Hope pool 40+","description":"Once per session at the start of your turn you may activate Fortress. While Fortress is active you pay Hope equal to your highest crest stat rank at the start of each of your turns instead of your normal maintenance cost â€” this covers your own Digimon's upkeep as well. All other allied Tamers pay half their normal per-turn Hope cost, rounded down, for as long as Fortress is active. Fortress ends when your Hope hits 0, when you choose to end it as a Free Action on your turn, or when the encounter ends. You carry the weight so nobody else has to."}}
{"_id":"eb1886b6a5304726","name":"I Won't Give Up","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Davis","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Sheer Stubbornness, Courage rank 5","description":"Once per session when your Digimon is reduced to 0 HP at Default Stage and would trigger the cascade, you may spend 8 Hope to refuse it. Your Digimon stays at 1 HP at their current Default Stage. Their Default Stage does not drop. They are still here. They are always still here."}}
{"_id":"eb2a77ec6118cbc2","name":"Not Flinching","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"TK S2","row":1,"expCost":300,"requirements":"Hope pool 20+ (any crest rank 4+)","description":"Once per encounter when your Digimon is targeted by an attack, you may spend 4 Hope to grant them +5 to their Reliability for that attack only. You have been in bad situations before. You know how to hold."}}
{"_id":"f2aa729d0899f32f","name":"Emotional Spike","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Yolei","row":2,"expCost":500,"requirements":"At least 1 Row 1 ability, Love rank 4","description":"Once per encounter when an ally Digimon is reduced to 0 HP in the same encounter, your Digimon immediately gains +4 to all attack rolls until the end of the round. Yolei does not handle loss quietly. Neither does her partner."}}
{"_id":"f5cca318d6747598","name":"One More Round","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Davis","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Tunnel Vision, Courage rank 5","description":"Once per encounter at the start of your turn, if your Digimon took damage last round, they gain temporary HP equal to your Courage rank. This happens automatically â€” you do not need to declare it. Getting hit just makes them more determined."}}
{"_id":"fd779619143e430a","name":"Weight of the Past","type":"classSkill","img":"icons/svg/ability.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"system":{"class":"Ken Redeemed","row":3,"expCost":700,"requirements":"Genius For Good, Knowledge rank 5","description":"Once per encounter as a Basic Action, choose one enemy Digimon. Make a Command check DN 13. On a success that Digimon takes -3 to all attack rolls for the rest of the encounter. You understand exactly how they think. You used to think the same way."}}
